---------------------------------------------------
All my changes to the kernel files can be found under "My Changes".

Simply search using a text editor.

---------------------------------------------------
The location is included in the filename.
Adjust the changes there to your kernel version.

---------------------------------------------------
Copy the following files there:

safer.c 	-> fs
safer_mmap.c	-> mm
safer_module.c	-> kernel/module



---------------------------------------------------
NEW: 20.04.2026
Check: Kernel Module
Check: Libraries

The files will be highlighted.

Flag in "Mem INODE"

See extension in "include/linux/fs.h"
"Structure Inode"

Checked files are marked.

Marked "Kernel Modules" and "Libraries"
are then not rechecked.

If files are deleted, erased, etc.,
the mark is removed.

A new check must be performed.


---------------------------------------------------
In the "safer.c" block, the flag is now also set in the inode.

This prevents a new hash calculation.
The flag also serves as an indicator for detecting "TOCTOU" attacks.

The "kernel_read_from_path" function continues to be used.
It performs basic parameter file checks, regardless of whether they include a shebang or not.



---------------------------------------------------
To compile the Linux kernel, the protection system must be used
disabled.

Or similar systems.

--------------------------------------------------
For your "Allowed" list, it's best to use /proc/safer.learning...
Copy it using the "cat" command.

You can control everything with the program "bsafer".











